{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"03ddfedc-fab9-4c59-a531-3b835171c265","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the unified `MSTest` v3 package (includes TestFramework, TestAdapter, Analyzers, and Test SDK)\n3. **Update TFM** — `net462` is supported but modern .NET is recommended\n\nYour test code (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert.*`) uses the same namespace and is fully compatible — no changes needed there.\n\nLet me apply the csproj changes:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Xy5DxVaBDuJmw52YJ8rXCt","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019GEaL5rqY5k5RZZWZuguJQ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-75efe945d6554cd48c24bed36a6288c4/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-75efe945d6554cd48c24bed36a6288c4/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"6ca4f4dd-315f-4154-b689-25d5a1023fef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n1. A .NET Framework 4.6.2 project (`net462`)\n2. An old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n3. `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` version 17.5.0\n4. Test code using `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3, they need to:\n\n1. **Update the target framework** - MSTest v3 requires at least .NET 6+ (it dropped .NET Framework support). Actually, let me check - MSTest v3 may still support .NET Framework. Let me think... MSTest 